title: Error deploying L1 contracts

-->

**Describe the bug**

Hello, I'm receiving this error during the [L1 contract deployment](https://stack.optimism.io/docs/build/getting-started/#deploy-the-l1-contracts) step of spinning up an op-stack rollup. Note I'm running a fully local dockerized system with docker-compose, L1 being a local hardhat node:
```
2023-10-20T07:56:53.035717Z ERROR apply:ext: evm::cheatcodes: non-empty stderr args=["bash", "-c", "jq -r '.transactions[] | select(.contractAddress == \"0x581f62c0901d4dce2553cb6140dBb4CeE533d834\") | select(.transactionType == \"CREATE\" or .transactionType == \"CREATE2\")' < /shared-contracts-bedrock/broadcast/Deploy.s.sol/31337/run-latest.json"] stderr="bash: line 1: /shared-contracts-bedrock/broadcast/Deploy.s.sol/31337/run-latest.json: No such file or directory\n"
```
(full error below)

**To Reproduce**
* Clone https://github.com/shaspitz/op-devnet
* Set `L1_SYNC_URL` in `.env` with ETH mainnet URL. 
* run `docker-compose up`
* Inspect coordinator with `docker logs op-devnet-coordinator-1`

**Expected behavior**
Contract deployment shouldn't error out.
